items.name: Surreality
items.description:
Please consider visiting my patreon, the first post is a full wildcard of my 1,240 prompts for this model. It's a fast track way to use my model for creativity and see the full potential.

See 1330 txt2img unprocessed samples from this model in an interactive mosaic here
https://mosaically.com/photomosaic/chaingirl-surreality

This is my surreal realism model. Surreality. This is my first release publicly but I've created models amongst friends and small community and directly for clients, but if people like this I will either extend it or create new models on other styles.

It's mostly SFW as it's trained directly on SD1.5 and has no merges.

Prompting

All my examples here are basic prompts. I left my stable diffusion webui generating 1k images with a wildcard of the prompts I trained. No cherry picking to upload, just grabbed any random images from the outputs. Use chaingirldark style when prompting

Sample prompts

  1. a path through a forest with lots of trees and lights on it's sides and a trail leading to the trees , chaingirldark style lightning storm, speedpainting, matte painting, concept art, 4k

  2. two horses running in a field in the foggy day time, with one horse looking at the camera , chaingirldark style ultra detailed, 8k, 35mm lens, beautiful, classical painting, smoke tendrils, clouds, foggy, volumetric lighting, cloudy, trending on Artstation, concept art, hyperdetailed, hyperrealistic

  3. a black and white photo of a church on a rocky hill with a stream running between it and a tree , chaingirldark style digital art, photorealistoc, art by greg rutkowski, hyperdetailed, western comic style, comic, comic style, sharp lineart, professional lighting, deviantart, artstation, trevor henderson, rossdtaws, cinematic, dramatic

  4. a desk with a computer and a monitor on it in a room with a lot of windows and plants , chaingirldark style cyberpunk 2077, blade runner, neon volumetric lights, 35mm lens, beautiful lighting, hyper detailed, digital art, trending in artstation

  5. a city street with a lot of flowers and buildings in the background at night time with pink and purple lights , chaingirldark style cyberpunk, futuristic, ultra detailed, concept art

  6. check example images metadata or my patreon wildcard for more prompts


    Negative prompt: boring, 3d render, long neck, out of frame, extra fingers, mutated hands, , ((poorly drawn hands)), 3DCG, cgstation, extra heads, close up, text ,watermarks, logo

Training:

Finetuned SD1.5 with 1200 surreal and sci-fi images. No merges.

  • trained chaining resolutions from low 300px up to 768px in increments

  • overall 36 epochs 29,970 steps when combining epoch's on lower res training with the 768 training

latina, blonde, asian, black, stockings, fishnets, tattoos, sucking cock,

If you enjoyed this model, please consider leaving a review. Your feedback helps develop better content. More Jiwenji Creations

Versioning history

major.minor.patch

major indicates a change in at least one of training data, tagging, or LoRA generation methodology. You can use the prompt from any image with the same major version and it will operate under similar conditions.


minor indicates nothing important unless indicated in release notes

patch indicates the number of training epochs, default is 1

items.description:

Capable of both male and female generations (leans more towards NSFW), though I never really generate many male centered images.

Future version may be implemented to help with hand generation (Hands are usually generated pretty well but not perfect).

None of the sample images have used controlnet or been impainted to show how the model truly performs.

All sample images have been generated using Euler a and upscaled with foolhardy_Remacri at denoising strength 0.3.

Additionally the sample images were generated with no VAE being used.

items.name: Sage - Dragon Quest III
items.description:
Number 3!

Sage was originally going to be my first Lora, but I suppose I preferred Priest's design, marginally, overall.

Tag: sage \(dq3\)

Like always, I cannot guarantee you'll get amazing results, but hopefully you'll find the model worth your time. I really like how this model came out, so I hope you do, as well.

Trained in: NAI this time! I feel like in my training that NAI gives me the most variation, but I still really like kotos for overall generations and samples.

Sample images a mix of multiple models that should pop up when you click on the full image.

Best weight to use is around: really anything, honestly. Sage was so gracious enough to be pretty flexible for me to use at just about any weight.

This was all generated locally on a 3070 RTX 8VRAM card.

Anomalies:

  • It's no secret that SD has trouble with weapons, so despite my best attempts, if you want weapons that don't look weird a fair amount of the time, please inpaint results you like!

  • Nothing much than that. Sage is a good girl, she generates pretty well, so have fun!

items.name: Ken Sugimori 1990s Classic Pokemon Trainers Style
items.description:
This LoRA aims to capture the style of early Ken Sugimori character concept art before his style was modernized with the Pokmon series' popularity.

If you are familiar with old Pokmon trainer cards, box art, and promotional and concept art before and during the release of the original Red, Green, and Blue games, this is that style.

=====
Training these models is expensive and time consuming.

If you like my work, consider supporting me on Patreon so I can continue making these in the future!

=====

Models were trained on Anythingv3 and tested on several anime checkpoint models. Examples were made with AbyssOrangeMixV2.

I have included 3 versions as they are all really good and have different strengths and weaknesses. For general use however, I recommend the latest version as it is the most flexible and coherent.

The trigger phrase is sugimori ken 1990s though in most cases, the models function fine even without the trigger phrase. Recommended weight is 0.8 to 1 with CLIP skip 2.

To use this LoRA with Automatic1111's Web UI, ensure that you are up to date and then just place the downloaded file(s) in the webui/models/lora directory.

  • I suggest using this LoRA at 0.8-1.0 weight for best results.

  • These images were generated and only tested using AOM2, AOM3 A1, OrangeMix VAE and AnythingV3 VAE.

  • Always add this to the prompt to activate it: arezu \(pokemon\)

  • It can do portraits, upper body and cowboy shot pretty well at 512x512

  • I suggest generating at 768x768 for higher quality pictures. It's also suggested using this resolution for full body.

All pictures were upscaled using these settings:

  • Upscaler: Fatal-Anime 4x

  • Hires. Steps: 25

  • Denoising Strength: 0.5

  • Upscale by 1.5

Known Issues (As of now)

  • It struggles with 'From Below' with certain poses.

  • Sometimes her hoodie and pants will swap colors -

  • It struggles with some poses (atleast the ones I've tried) - It helps to lower weight to 0.85-0.9.

Embeds and LoRAs used

items.name: Jennifer Connelly (80s/90s)
items.description:
Jennifer Connelly is an American actress, known for many roles in films such as Labyrinth, Career Opportunities, Hulk and Requiem for a Dream, among many others. She won an Oscar for Best Supporting Actress for her role in A Beautiful Mind (2001).

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Updated! Please check the "About this version" section for more info.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (jg_jc0n:0.99), a woman, (sfw tight fashion shirt:1.2), (long jeans), in a departmentn store, natural light, (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1), (painted lips)"

modelVersions.name: v2.1
modelVersions.description: Retrained from scratch with a new dataset. This time I managed to get ahold of a few decent quality pics, and I think that shows in the final result. The embedding I'm uploading is step 1850. I trained at a 0.004 learning rate until step 1000. From there to step 2500, at a 0.001 rate. There were signs of saturation from very early on the training process, but by simply reducing the embedding weight in the prompt to 0.99 you will get rid of most of said saturation.

But the pics I could get were mostly low res, and that shows in the final result, which I'm still quite happy with, but I know probably doesn't do Jennifer justice. The images I picked are from her "Career Opportunities" era. That is, early 90s, a time in which she was probably the most beautiful woman to walk on Earth.

items.name: Cheval Grand (umamusume)
items.description:
LoHa of Cheval Grand (umamusume). Please install extension on WebUI.

After installing extension, put LoHa file in your sd/models/lora folder and use LoRA notation in prompt to applying LoHa. <lora:loha_name:weight>

All of my works is free. If you'd like to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee.

Recommended options

  • LoRA weight around 0.7

  • Trigger words

    • Base

      • cheval grand \(umamusume\)

    • Racing competition costume :

      • long sleeves, cape, sailor collar, white shirt, yellow ascot, white jacket, white gloves, belt, black shorts, black socks, shoes, white footwear

    • Tracen summer uniform

      • tracen school uniform, summer uniform, serafuku, puffy short sleeves, bowtie, horseshoe ornament, sailor collar, sailor shirt, frills, white skirt, purple shirt, miniskirt, zettai ryouiki, white thighhighs, brown footwear, shoes

    • Casual :

      • She has no official casual clothes

    • Other clothes :

      • Baseball sports wear :

        • alternate costume, white headwear, short over long sleeves, white shirt, sportswear, baseball uniform, belt, white pants, socks, shoes, black footwear

      • Casual ?

        • causal, denim jacket, white shirt, black pants

        • grey hoodie, hands in pocket, clothes writing, black pants

Use a model derived from or mixed with animefull model.

  • Settings

    • Stable Diffusion WebUI by Automatic1111

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • I recommend kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • Use Hires.fix to get higher quality image

      • Upscaler

        • Latent, Latent (nearest-exact), Latent (bicubic antialiased) or other Latent series.

      • Denoising strength 0.50~0.65

LoRA training info

  • trained on sd-scripts by kohya_ss.

    • LyCORIS by KohakuBlueleaf

    • Thank you all a lot!

  • based on Animefull-pruned model

  • 37 images of

    • 4x low quality 10 images

    • 8x medium quality 13 images

    • 16x high quality 14 images

    • => 1 epoch = 368 images

  • replaced character feature tags with cheval grand \(umamusume\)

    • 1girl, hair between eyes, short hair, hat, tail, brown hair, green eyes, simple background, solo, horse ears, streaked hair, animal ears, bangs, horse girl, white headwear, black hair, medium hair, white hair, horse tail, blue eyes, multicolored hair, two-tone hair, ears through headwear

    • I think these tags are

      • the essentials of Cheval Grand

      • or unnecessary for training because of duplication.

  • resolution : 768x768 with aspect ratio bucketing.

  • other training settings is included in training_data.zip or metadata in LoRA file.

All uploaded images are generated by AOM3A1

And, special thanks to my best friend. DH.

items.name: Ufotable / Fate Series ( Style LoRA/LyCORIS )
items.description:
Making models is costing me my children's tuition. Do you like what I do? Feel free to buy me a coffee

This LoRA was made due to the request of KoRo#8133 and as a Ufotable Enjoyer I complied. Also, thanks to KoRo#8133 for gathering the dataset for this. Also credit to all the amazing artists at Ufotable who worked on these projects without which this would not be possible. Moving on, I used Anything V4.5 as a base model for training. This LoRA was trained on more than 100 Images of Ufotable's Artstyle (Backgrounds, Characters, etc). Either way and it turned out well so I hope you like it.

You don't need the negative embeddings used in the example prompts, but if you want the exact quality of Images I have you can download the negative embeddings from here https://huggingface.co/Sikinx/UfotableLoRAFiles/tree/main

and paste them in the "embeddings" folder in your WebUI directory.

It's flexible enough to make all kinds of stuff but please, If you want to make specific characters, use LoRA's for them and proper prompts. You can prompt well Known Fate Characters (Saber etc) and it does them just fine. Please check the examples.

Please be aware that while the LoRA itself is quite flexible with various weights. I recommend that you go below 0.6 LoRA weight as it results in more pleasant looking gens but still keeps a bit of the artstyle. You may try different configs and find whatever works best for you. However if you want the exact style I have then the weight I used for the examples is "0.9".

The trigger words for the LoRA are "ufotable style, anime coloring, anime screencap" as included on the model page as well. Works great on Anything V4.5, or on any anime model out there. Altough you might need to play around with the settings abit.

Also, if you can get the best looking results I recommend you use Anything V3 or Anything V4.5 Vae.

Please enjoy and consider supporting me.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight according to the instructions (by default it's :1)
